>Lastly, armed with knowledge of y_1, y_2 and W(x) I should be able to 
>compute Y(x) - the general solution of the non-homogeneous d.e. using 
>the formula:
>
>
>     Y(x) = y_2 * int(x_0 to x)[(y_1(t) * g(t)/W(t)]dt  -
>            y_1 * int(x_0 to x)[(y_2(t) * g(t))/W(t)]dt
>
>Where g(x) = (12x^2 - 6x)/(4x^2 - x)
