Hi Martin,

Thanks for writing to Dr Math.  So your question is how to integrate

  int[2(2x - 1)/(4x^2 -x)]dx

First factor the denominator as

  x*(4x-1),

and then use partial fractions to write this in the form

  2(2x - 1)/(4x^2 -x) = A/x + B/(4x-1)

for some real numbers A and B.  Then integrate the last expression.

If you have any questions about this or need more help, please write
back and show me what you have been able to do, and I will try to
offer further suggestions.

- Doctor Vogler, The Math Forum
